article.headline: Harvard 84, Vermont 76 (OT)
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Brian Cusworth scored a career-high 25 points and tied his career best with 16 rebounds and Drew Housman added a career-high 25 points to lead Harvard to an 84-76 overtime victory over Vermont Sunday. Harvard trailed by nine in the second half, but came back to force overtime. Joe Trapani, who finished with 20 points, made two 3-pointers to give Vermont a 49-40 lead with 16:09 remaining. But Harvard went on a 14-3 run, ending with two free throws by Housman, to take a 54-52 lead with 11 minutes to play. Vermont committed offensive fouls on five of seven possessions during the stretch. The score was tied at 69 at the end of regulation. Cusworth and Housman scored the first seven points in overtime for Harvard, which held on by making 11 of 16 free throws to end the game. Jim Goffredo added 18 points for Harvard (7-4). Chris Holm scored 17 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for Vermont (5-5).
